Delicious. I hope this review doesn't appear 2x, I think I pushed the wrong button somewhere. Anyway, adjust flavors to make it perfect for you, great advice contained in other reviews. Make this with one pot by sprinkling flour directly over veg and let that cook a few mins, then deglaze with liquids. If you add liquids slowly enough, you will have no lumps. Then at the end put the crumb topping on top of the skillet (same pan) and put the whole thing in the oven. 1 Pan. Oh, except for the pasta pan, you do need to boil the pasta. So 2 pans. Still better than the 4 they call for in the recipe. Hope this is helpful.

