Rating: 3
This is a very good basic recipe, but can be made a four-forker without too much trouble..... How? This was my approach: Add 1 1/2 tsp Dijon mustard to the butter prior to adding the flour for the sauce. When the sauce is finished add cayenne pepper to taste and 1/2 tsp nutmeg. When combining the sauce and mushroom mixture, add one bunch of finely chopped flat-leaf parsley and a hand full or two of frozen peas. Use 3/4 cup of Cheddar cheese for the topping (I used Old Amsterdam, since that's readily available in Holland already grated) and 1/4 cup grated parmesan or Pecorino cheese. The difference is significant when compared to the original recipe!

