Rating: 4
I LOVE this recipeit's so versatile, fun to embellish, and so great as-written, and it's become my go-to for tuna noodle casserole. I like to stir in veggies before roastingfrozen or canned peas, fresh zucchini, red peppers (either fresh or roasted), and broccoli are all favorites. Here's a way to make this dish DAIRY FREE: Sub in dairy-free margarine like Earth Balance for butter Use unsweetened almond milk instead of milk for the rouxit blends best and tastes great Use Daiya or Teese cheddar cheese for the topping, or, if you can tolerate it, cheddar made from raw goat's milk. I know most lactose intolerant folk are used to making these simple substitutions, but if you were wondering if it would work, let me tell you - it does!

