Rating: 4
This has become classic comfort food in our household. Ive taken a bunch of suggestions from other people, and changed the assembly order to reduce the dishes and make the timing a bit more efficient, so here goes: First cook the pasta, and rinse it till its thoroughly cooled, leaving it in the colander. Then in a 2.5L saucepan, I do the mushroom paragraph, adding 2 stalks of celery, chopped pretty fine. Then move that into a large bowl, and use the same saucepan for the roux. I use the liquid from the tuna as part of the two cups for the roux broth. As youre making the roux (and I warm the 1% or 2% milk a little in the measuring cup), flake into the mushroom mixture 2 cans of tuna, some parsley, about 5 oz of frozen peas (1/2 a box), and the lemon juice. Season lots w/ salt & pepper; thyme goes well too. When the roux is thickened, mix in half the cheese, then combine with the mushroom, etc& and pour into the casserole. Finally, thank you pastaguy  the suggestion for substituting potato chips as a topper is BRILLIANT! I mix the other half of the cheese in w/ the crushed chips (which you can do in the same saucepan once you remove the roux), and use that as a topping.

