Wow! I was hesitant to make this because I was missing three key ingredients... soy sauce, chicken stock and sherry. I decided to risk it, using lightly salted water in place of the chicken stock, sherry vinegar in place of the sherry, and a paste of miso and water in place of the soy sauce. This is obviously a very forgiving recipe, because it was still delicious. Aside from the subs I mentioned above, I used peas instead of mushrooms, two cans of tuna instead of one, mixed a bit of the grated cheddar directly into the warm sauce before pouring it on the noodles, and used a combination of croutons and bread crumbs for the topping. My boyfriend is incredibly picky, but he raved and raved about this casserole. For those who stated that this was bland..I think the key is to take enough time to properly cook the flour when making the roux, and then making sure to season the sauce well to your liking before mixing in the tuna. I will make this again and again.

