This was a production to make but worth the effort! Instead of using fresh mushrooms, I used dried porcinis, reconstituted them in 1.5 cups of hot water, and reserved the mushroom water. I diced the reconstituted porcinis finely and tossed them in the saute. I used the broth from the mushrooms as one of the two cups of chicken broth. This gave it such a wonderful mushroomy flavor...I also used skim milk and it comes out great. Another sub I made was using sake instead of sherry...it offers a nice, nutty flavor to the casserole, but sherry also worked fine. Thank GOODNESS I was out of canned mushroom soup and found this recipe!

