Rating: 3
I avoid tuna, due to the mercury content, so I decided to make a salmon noodle casserole. I used three cans of salmon (next time I'll use fresh poached salmon). Since it was water-packed, I added one tablespoon of Olive Oil to the sauce. I doubled both the soy sauce and the sherry (I used dry sherry). Next time, I will also double (possibly triple) the lemon juice, as well. I also added a half cup of milk due to the extra salmon (I was concerned about the possibility of it being dry). For breadcrumbs, I substituted what I had on hand -- Italian-spiced Panko, which really added to the flavor and the herbed crunch was delicious! Since I bought my egg noodles in bulk, I misjudged and used too much, so next time I will reduce the amount. I increased the amount of cheese to suit my housemates' palate and added garlic, peas and white pepper to the mix. Next time, I'm considering broccoli or green beans instead of peas. Overall, it was very tasty and with a few more minor adjustments (mostly noted above) I would definitely make this again.

