Today I had a craving for Tuna Noodle Casserole, which I haven't had in years. Seems the previous reviewer was on the same wavelength - must be our lovely Seattle winter weather! I ALMOST chickened out and made the canned-soup recipe I grew up on. Glad I listened to the rave reviews for this recipe instead. It really hit the spot and will definitely make it onto my comfort food repertoire. I made the popular modifications of adding a bit of garlic and Tobasco to the mushrooms. Also used crushed croutons for topping. The whole thing took me about 30 minutes to put together. I used pre-sliced mushrooms and did not bother cooking the egg noodles. They cooked perfectly in the oven. I made the mushroom saute and the roux/sauce at the same time. Served with white wine and green salad w/champagne vinagrette. Mmmmmm. Next time maybe I'll double the recipe and make an extra one to freeze.

