I'm shocked at any negative review - I don't know how anyone could NOT love this! Adding diced celery & 1/2c walnuts (because it was something my Mom always added to her tuna casserole) only added a few minutes to the prep time, and lots of flavor. I topped it with 1 cup of crushed kettle potato chips, and used "Kluski" noodles, which, with the nuts and celery, made it taste more like Mom's. It took just a few minutes more to make this recipe than one that uses the salty, processed canned soup (which I HATE). With my personal changes, this will be the Tuna Casserole recipe that I'll make for the rest of my life. The sherry, soy sauce and chicken stock give this dish lots of flavor, as well as the fresh mushrooms. Great Recipe!

