My 16 year old daughter requested this dish over the weekend, so to find it, a-searching the recipe data base I went. This recipe is all it is advertized and more. Following the lead of a couple of the other reviewers listed here, I also took some liberties with the recipe. I didn't want to go to the store on Monday evening so I adlibbed a bit. I doubled the amount of tuna as was suggested. Then I substituted Marsala wine for the sherry, used purple onion instead of what was specified and finally, instead of flat noodles, I used up the contents of several different partially empty pasta boxes from the pantry. I think I ended up with a combination of rotelli and the little tubes, what ever they are called, plus some bow-ties in the casserole dish. Well, the it came out superbly and my daughter and her friends all seconds. Me too. Their only comment was that I should have added a third can of tuna. The dish was moist, very flavorful and not as heavy as some of the cream based casseroles of my mother's era. I will definitely make this again.

