Rating: 3
I finally liked a tuna casserole! I did make a few modifications though. I sauteed the onion and mushrooms in olive oil instead of butter, and only used 2 tbsp butter in the roux. I also added frozen peas before baking and I skipped the topping entirely. This had good flavor and I will definitely make it again.

Rating: 3
this took a while, so make it with a friend to reduce time, otherwise i might have considered buying cream of mushroom soup. however, i tasted it 3/4 of the way thru, and it gave a warm hug only comfort food provides. i subbed hungarian tokaji aszu (dessert wine)for the sherry, and ponzu in place of soy sauce. sprinkled a little mexican oregano ontop just before baking, and used two cans of tuna instead of one for more meat. used little ripped pieces of french bread for topping. used regular macaroni (1/2 ditali, 1/2 mini pene)instead of egg noodles. added a few generous dashes of creole seasoning during final correction. serving with a mesculn salad, wine & french bread.

