People that dismiss this recipe as "simplistic" or "old-fashioned" are missing the point. This is comfort food, and invokes food memories. My mother made tuna noodle casserole with Kraft Mac 'n Cheese, a can of tuna, and frozen peas. It was fast and good (believe it or not), AND it allowed our family to sit down together and eat on a weeknight. I like doing something interesting and different as a cook as much as anyone (FYI: don't try to make your own tamarind juice), but simple can be good and sometimes the best. Create your own signature dish to pass on to your kids. Mine is Poppy-seed Chicken, but I'm not sharing.... :)

