Rating: 4
it is so delicious and the time spent to make it is so worthwhile.

Rating: 3
I could tell from the ingredients it was going to be a bit bland so I added extra flavor where I could. I used crimini mushrooms, I added some fresh thyme, lots of fresh cracked pepper and also some frozen peas, all of which complemented the dish well. I didn't have any sherry on hand so I used white wine instead, that seemed to work fine. I also used Japanese Panko breadcrumbs (found in boxes in the Asian section of the supermarket) for extra texture and crunch. After it came out of the oven I sprinkled some finely chopped flat leaf parsley on top for color. Overall, this turned out to be a pretty classy version of a tuna casserole. To save a little on cleanup, I added the butter/flour/broth directly into the same pan with the mushrooms, instead of using a separate pan as the recipe states. This seemed to work just fine. Looks like this is a recipe that you could make quite a few variations on and still have it turn out nicely.

Rating: 3
This was well worth all the clean up and time needed to make. Absolutely delicious. The only weakness of the recipe is that there just isn't enough tuna. Next time I make it I'll try adding two cans.

Rating: 4
